<h5 class="font-weight-bold">Action Bar - General</h5>
<div class="row mt-5">

        <div class="col-sm-6">
            <p><%= image_tag("/design-system/photography/dw-actionbar-general.png", alt: "Action Bar - General") %></p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-sm-6">

            <h5 class="font-weight-bold mb-5">Action Bar - Layout and Rules</h5>

            <p>The action bar is meant to be flexible enough  to account for each property, their seasonal changes, and the types of users interacting with them. On desktop it should span the length of  the browser, on mobile it will be housed within  an expand/collapse state.
            </p>
            
            <p>For Dollywood, we have included the following:</p> 

            <p><strong>Park hours:</strong> this area should highlight hours or messaging if the parks are closed.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Where to?:</strong> this dropdown allows for the selection of which park the user wants to visit. Theme Park, Water Park, Both Parks.</p>
            
            <p><strong>When?:</strong> this dropdown houses a calendar that allows the user to select when & how many days.</p>
            
            <p><strong>How Many?:</strong> this dropdown allows for selection of the number of guests and their age range from adult, child, or senior.</p>


            </div>
</div>

<hr class="mt-5">
